<p>The cost of getting this wrong is specific and measurable. Teams that treat PR and social as separate channels spend 40–60% more per earned link while capturing less than half the potential branded search lift. They earn coverage, then let it die. Meanwhile, competitors who connect the two disciplines compound their visibility with every campaign.</p>
